--This host of kafka cluster we can give 2 3 host nae so if anyone will be down it will connect with other....

##spring.kafka.producer.bootstrap.servers=localhost:9092.localhost:9094

This is for to serialize the Key.....
##spring.kafka.producer.key-serializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringSerializer

This is for to Serialize the Value
##spring.kafka.producer.value-serializer=org.springframework.kafka.support.serializer.JsonSerializer

This is for to get the acks from all the broker that message is written successfully or not

##spring.kafka.producer.acks=all & -1/0/1

all means to get acks from all broker
1 means to get acks from master broker
0 means don't expect any acks from any broker Just fire and forget
By default will get the acks from leader broker

##spring.kafka.producer.retries=10

This is for How many times kafka will retry to send message to broker if broker has some failure for short time
By default retries count is very large 2147483647 (INTEGER.MAX_VALUES)


##spring.kafka.producer.properties.retry.backoff.ms=1000

This is for how long producer will wait before attempting to retry a failed request. Default value is 100ms

##spring.kafka.producer.properties.delivery.timeout.ms=120000

The maximum time producer will spend trying to deliver the message.Default value is 120000(2Min)
This time is for entire process....

+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Delivery timeout ms >= linger.ms + request.timeout.ms
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

###spring.kafka.producer.properties.linger.ms=0

The maximum time Producer will wait and buffer data before sending a batch of messages.The default value is 0
means as soon as producer will get data it will publish that message but when will add linger.ms then for that time
Producer ill wait to accumulate more data and it will send it into batch

We can also use compression to compress the data and send so t will increase the throughput of producer....like gzip , snappy
+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

##spring.kafka.producer.request.timeout.ms=3000

The maximum time that producer will wait for a response from the broker after sending a request.
The default value is 30000(30s)


##spring.kafka.producer.properties.enable.idempotence=true

This property will ensure that while sending message to kafka broker if any failure will occur before acks
so it will retry for multiple time but massage will publish only once.......

In Kafka newer version by default this is enabled as true..

##spring.kafka.producer.max.in.flight.requests.per.connection=5

This property in Producer means that kafka will send 5message at once without waiting for acks..if in case of failure
it will retry...and order of message will be same order will not get changed




